on, D.H., Soil respiration and georespiration distinguished by transport analyses of vadose CO2, 13CO2, and 14CO2 (1998) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 12 (2), pp. 361-372; Kirita, H., Re-examination of the absorption method of measuring soil respiration under field conditions. II. Combined effect of the covered ground area and the surface area of KOH solution on CO2 absorption rates (1971) Jpn. J. Ecol., 21, pp. 43-47; Kucera, C.L., Kirkham, D.R., Soil respiration studies in a tallgrass prairie in Missouri (1971) Ecology, 52, pp. 912-915; Lavigne, M.B., Ryan, M.G., Growth and maintenance respiration rates of aspen, black spruce and jack pine stems at northern and southern BOREAS sites (1997) Tree Physiol., 17, pp. 543-551; Leffelaar, P.A., Dynamic simulation of multinary diffusion problems related to soil (1987) Soil Sci., 143, pp. 79-91; Lundegaardh, H., Carbon dioxide evolution of soil surface and crop growth (1927) Soil Sci., 23, pp. 417-453; McGinn, S.M., Akinremi, O.O., McLean, H.D.J., Ellert, B., An automated chamber system for measuring soil respiration (1998) Can. J. Soil Sci., 78 (4), pp. 573-579; Mielnick, P.C., Dugas, W.A., Soil CO2 flux in a tallgrass prairie (2000) Soil Biochem., 32 (2), pp. 221-228; Millington, R.J., Quirk, J.P., Permeability of porous solids (1961) Trans. Faraday Soc., 57, pp. 1200-1207; Minderman, G., Vulvo, J.C., Comparison of techniques for the measurement of carbon dioxide evolution from soil (1973) Pedobiologia, 13, pp. 73-80; Nakadai, T., Koizumi, H., Usami, Y., Satoh, M., Oikawa, T., Examamination of the methods for measuring soil respiration in cultivated land: Effect of carbon dioxide concentration on soil respiration (1993) Ecol. Res., 8, pp. 65-71; Nay, S.M., Bormann, B.T., Soil carbon changes: Comparing flux monitoring and mass balance in a box lysimeter experiment (2000) Soil Sci. Soc. Am. J., 64 (3), pp. 943-948; Nay, S.M., Matteson, K.G., Bormann, B.T., Biases of chamber methods for measuring soil CO2 efflux demonstrated w